t Finley Graves and Vice President for Finance and Administration Bob Brown, the group leaders are: Terri Day, Vice Provost for Academic Administration Brandi Renton, Assistant Vice President for Organizational Behavior Debbie Rohwer, Presidential Faculty Fellow and Chair/Professor of Music Education The group will include representatives, as needed, from different colleges, divisions and departments. The Talon Team will gather input from the faculty and staff through the form below. If you experience organizational, functional or process problems at the university, division or department level that negatively affect the university or your work, you can fill out the form and describe the challenges you're facing. The Talon Team will respond with a plan to address the concerns, starting with the most urgent issues first. To submit an issue, please fill out each field with a brief description of the problem so the Talon Team has the basic information. If you have questions, you can contact Talon.Team@unt.edu. Process improvement resolution will be dependent on the nature of the improvement. Please allow time for processing and review. Regardless of the severity of the issue, you can expect a reply updating you on a plan of action or a resolution.   First Name * Last Name * Email * College (if applicable) Department/Division Phone Please provide a description of the problem to be investigated Please describe the steps that have already been taken to remedy this problem Please attach any documentation to help us investigate the problem Please list the names and contact information for anyone else who may be able to provide context for this problem * Information is required to follow up on the problem identified. Personal information only will be used for fact-gathering purposes. Initiatives & Priorities Top-Tier Research University Planning Implementation Talon Team Follow @UNTPrez UNT Insider President's News Roundup Learn more about UNT Partner with UNT University Awa